      {
        "id": 2761320,
        "name": "Jonathan Loesberg",
        "username": "Jonathan_Loesberg",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/9de053/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2019-11-27T16:22:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>While a lot of 07s are very forward, enough for many people to be a fault, others have been quite desultory. The last time I tasted Ferrand, it was the latter. I would open it a few hours in advance and taste it and depending on how you like the state it\u2019s in, either pour out a four oz. glass and let everything breathe, decant for a couple of hours or, if you think the wine is ready, just leave the bottle as is.</p>",
